# OMS-HRM Project Rules (Index)

This repo is a **Laravel 13 + Inertia v3 + React 19** monolith with company-scoped Spatie permissions. Do not introduce REST APIs, React Query, global state stores, or Eloquent policies.

## Domain rule files

| Area | Rule file |
|------|-----------|
| Shared UI | `.cursor/rules/components.mdc` |
| Inertia pages | `.cursor/rules/pages.mdc` |
| Hooks | `.cursor/rules/hooks.mdc` |
| Forms | `.cursor/rules/forms.mdc` |
| Tables | `.cursor/rules/tables.mdc` |
| Dialogs & sheets | `.cursor/rules/dialogs.mdc` |
| Data & routing | `.cursor/rules/api.mdc` |
| Authorization | `.cursor/rules/permissions.mdc` |
| PHP / Laravel | `.cursor/rules/backend.mdc` |
| TypeScript | `.cursor/rules/typescript.mdc` |
| Performance | `.cursor/rules/performance.mdc` |
| Tests | `.cursor/rules/testing.mdc` |

## Non-negotiables

- Extend existing abstractions before creating new ones.
- Domain logic → `app/Support/`; integrations → `app/Services/`.
- UI in `resources/js/features/`; keep `resources/js/pages/` thin.
- Every change needs a targeted Pest test.
- Run `vendor/bin/pint --dirty` after PHP edits.

